<p><img src="/assets/img/rust/wallset-onefetch.png" alt="Wallset onefetch" /></p>

<p>The repo information is displayed next to the ASCII logo for the dominant language. You can also configure Onefetch to use an image (png, jpeg …) in the supported terminals with the <code class="highlighter-rouge">-i</code> parameter and indicating the image address, example:</p>
<blockquote>
  <p>Remembering that only <a href="https://en.terminalroot.com.br/the-10-best-terminal-emulators-for-your-linux/">terminal emulators</a>: <code class="highlighter-rouge">xterm</code>, <code class="highlighter-rouge">mlterm</code> and <code class="highlighter-rouge">kitty</code> are supported</p>
</blockquote>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">onefetch <span class="nt">-i</span> path/to/image.jpg</code></pre></figure>

<p><img src="/assets/img/rust/onefetch.png" alt="Image Onefetch" /></p>

<p>For more information, consult the <a href="https://github.com/o2sh/onefetch/">project repository</a>.</p>

